  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Defect Repair Latency is a measurement of the average turnaround time for a defect to be corrected. It helps the team&#xD;
    understand the effectiveness and efficiency of their testing and defect removal efforts, verifying whether defects are&#xD;
    being addressed in a timely manner in-process and post-ship.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3 align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    To calculate the average gap between recognition and fixing of defects:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Total Number of Defects/ Total Time to Fix Defects&#xD;
&lt;/p>A good way to monitor Defect Repair Latency over time is to use a trend line. Average time is plotted on the Y axis,&#xD;
and iterations are plotted on the X axis. Plot separate trend lines for each severity level (e.g. critical, average,&#xD;
minor).&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Following are two example Defect Repair Latency Charts. The first graph,&amp;nbsp;provides Post-Ship data,&amp;nbsp;shows the&#xD;
    average defect repair latency in term of turnaround time in days. The second graph does the same using Pre-Ship data.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Defect Repair Latency Pre-Ship&quot; src=&quot;./resources/defect_repair_latency_preship.gif&quot; width=&quot;429&quot;&#xD;
    height=&quot;379&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Defect Repair Latency Post-Ship&quot; src=&quot;./resources/defect_repair_latency_postship.gif&quot; width=&quot;430&quot;&#xD;
    height=&quot;385&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    The expected trend is that higher severity defects are resolved more quickly than those with lower severity. The&#xD;
    average time to resolve should be within the acceptable range for the project with no unreasonable maximum values.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    When monitored during the lifecycle, time spent repairing defects can provide an indication to project management of&#xD;
    how long it will take to get the system release-ready, how difficult it might be to maintain post-ship, and how much&#xD;
    cost might be impacted.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    When monitored post-ship, time spent repairing defects can help the team understand the impact to product reliability,&#xD;
    availability, and the customer's perception of value.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Several factors impact the average time to repair defects:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Poor defect management processes&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Low priority placed on debugging during development, so defects are addressed late and are more difficult to fix&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Not enough resources assigned to retesting efforts, slow response times by developers&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Frequency and reporting&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Data should be harvested at the end of each iteration and reviewed by project management to identify trends.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Defect Repair Latency is captured in IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; QualityManager&amp;reg;. IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Insight&amp;reg; reports on this metric.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Assumptions and prerequisites&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Defect tracking system is in place that captures each submitted defect with its severity&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Pitfalls, advice, and countermeasures&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;span style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-fareast-language: JA&quot;>For this metric to be useful,&#xD;
            targets should be set for defect repair turnaround according to severity. Monitor trends for comparison with&#xD;
            the targets.&lt;/span>&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        &lt;div style=&quot;MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto&quot; class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;span style=&quot;FONT-FAMILY: Arial; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-fareast-language: JA&quot;>Use Customer Satisfaction as a&#xD;
            countermeasure for this metric. If average response times are within team targets, but customers are not happy,&#xD;
            it could be that they are waiting too long for defect resolutions.&lt;/span>&lt;br />&#xD;
        &lt;/div>&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></mainDescription>
